    description: 'The unsworn. In a world built on oaths, you refuse to take one.',
    lore: 'In the Shattered Provinces, every institution demands fealty. The houses require sworn service. The Church requires doctrinal obedience. The mercenary companies require contracts. You refuse. Maybe you were burned by the oath system: a house that demanded loyalty and repaid it with disgrace. Maybe you saw what oaths do to people, how Stonemark rigidity and Veldran ledgers consume the person behind the promise. Maybe you simply believe that loyalty given under obligation is no loyalty at all. The reason for refusal varies; the refusal itself is the position.\nStart with one contact from a former house at Hostile (the people who remember what you were before you walked away). One underworld contact at Favorable (the networks of the unsworn who trade freely because they owe nothing). Advantage on checks involving survival outside institutional structures and on dealings with multiple factions simultaneously, because you are beholden to none of them. Disadvantage on initial social checks with any landed house: the Oathless are distrusted not for what they did, but for what they refuse to do. In a world of sworn bonds, the unsworn are the only truly unpredictable people.',
